properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 2:41PM CST until February 17 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...PRECIPITATION SPREADING FARTHER NORTHEAST...

.A Winter Weather Advisory has been expanded northward and until 6
PM for areas east of a line from Fairmont to Mankato and Eagan,
which includes Scott and Dakota Counties. This advisory also
remains in effect until 9 PM for Freeborn, Steele, and Goodhue
counties in Minnesota, and for Pepin and Eau Claire counties in
Wisconsin. The advisory is based on snowfall amounts of one to
three inches, with locally heavier amounts along the Iowa border
this afternoon.

Precipitation will expand farther to the northeast across east
central Minnesota this afternoon. It will also linger into the
early evening as this system has slowed down a few hours.

A period of light snow, occasionally heavy at times, will spread
across south central, and east central Minnesota, and into west
central Wisconsin through the early evening. The snow will end
by 9 PM in west central Wisconsin.

* WHAT...Snow. Snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches.

* WHERE...Scott and Dakota Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. This will affect the
evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
